WEBVTT

00:00.400 --> 00:02.567
♪ WHEN THIS BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:02.567 --> 00:05.500
♪ BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:05.500 --> 00:09.867
♪ WANDERIN' DOWN THIS ROAD
THAT WE CALL LIFE ♪

00:09.867 --> 00:12.133
♪ IS WHAT WE'RE DOIN' ♪

00:12.133 --> 00:14.000
♪ IT'S GOOD TO KNOW
I HAVE FRIENDS ♪

00:14.000 --> 00:15.800
♪ WHO WILL ALWAYS ♪

00:15.800 --> 00:18.200
♪ STAND BY ME ♪

00:18.200 --> 00:20.934
♪ WHEN THIS BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:20.934 --> 00:23.867
I DO NOT WANT TO GO
TO NEW YORK!

00:23.867 --> 00:25.033
WHAT ABOUT TOPANGA?

00:25.033 --> 00:26.400
WHO CARES ABOUT --

00:26.400 --> 00:28.800
WHY DOES EVERYONE
ALWAYS TAKE TOPANGA'S SIDE?!

00:28.800 --> 00:30.900
TOPANGA?

00:30.900 --> 00:33.967
GIVE ME YOUR HAND.

00:36.600 --> 00:37.967
WHY?

00:37.967 --> 00:40.467
I WANT TO SEE
IF OUR ENERGIES CONVERGE.

00:42.100 --> 00:46.200
[ LAUGHING ]

00:46.200 --> 00:47.500
[ GASPS ]

00:47.500 --> 00:51.133
YOU'RE NOT GONNA, LIKE,
<i>KISS </i>ME NOW, ARE YOU?

00:51.133 --> 00:53.734
WOULD IT BE
YOUR FIRST KISS?

00:53.734 --> 00:57.600
YOU SHOULDN'T KISS SOMEBODY
YOU'RE NOT MARRIED TO.

00:57.600 --> 00:59.100
HMM.

00:59.100 --> 01:03.000
YEAH, I WOULD HAVE TO FEEL
I REALLY KNEW THE PERSON...

01:03.000 --> 01:04.600
AND THAT I LIKED HIM.

01:04.600 --> 01:06.600
GOOD.

01:06.600 --> 01:08.600
GOOD.

01:22.767 --> 01:25.600
IT WAS MY FIRST ONE, TOO.

01:31.567 --> 01:33.500
I DID IT.

01:33.500 --> 01:37.700
I JOINED THE PEACE CORPS.

01:37.700 --> 01:39.400
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

01:39.400 --> 01:42.200
YEAH, I'M GONNA SIT IN A HUT
AND EAT MUD.

01:42.200 --> 01:45.000
IT'S A PLAN, ALL RIGHT?

01:45.000 --> 01:46.367
MY STEPDAD THINKS HE'S
GONNA TEACH <i>ME </i>A LESSON?

01:46.367 --> 01:48.600
NO, NO, <i>I'M </i>GONNA TEACH
<i>HIM A LESSON. </i>

01:48.600 --> 01:49.934
OH, CORY.

01:49.934 --> 01:52.600
HEY, I'VE BEEN DOING
SOME THINKING ABOUT NEW YORK.

01:52.600 --> 01:54.600
I'M GONNA DO
SOME THINKING, TOO.

01:54.600 --> 01:56.867
LET ME TELL YOU
WHAT WE'RE GONNA DO --

01:56.867 --> 01:58.934
THIS IS WHERE OUR FRIENDS ARE,
WHERE WE GREW UP.

01:58.934 --> 02:00.400
THIS IS
WHERE WE SHOULD STAY.

02:00.400 --> 02:01.967
I'M GONNA TURN DOWN
THE INTERNSHIP.

02:01.967 --> 02:03.900
I WANT TO DO
WHATEVER YOU WANT.

02:03.900 --> 02:06.233
I WAS REALLY
LOOKING FORWARD TO GOING,

02:06.233 --> 02:08.000
BUT IF YOU
DON'T WANT TO GO...

02:10.233 --> 02:13.400
I THINK WE SHOULD STAY HERE.
I'LL SEE YOU AT HOME?

02:13.400 --> 02:15.300
WHERE WE LIVE.

02:18.767 --> 02:19.767
YES!

02:19.767 --> 02:20.767
AAH!
AAH!

02:20.767 --> 02:21.767
AAH!
AAH!

02:21.767 --> 02:22.767
HEY!

02:22.767 --> 02:23.767
KA-CHING!
KA-CHING!

02:23.767 --> 02:25.567
YEAH! WHOO!

02:25.567 --> 02:28.400
THANK YOU!

02:28.400 --> 02:30.700
WE'RE NOT MOVING TO NEW YORK,
SHAWNIE!

02:30.700 --> 02:32.100
NOTHING'S GONNA CHANGE!

02:32.100 --> 02:33.934
SHE DIDN'T MEAN A WORD
SHE SAID.

02:33.934 --> 02:35.800
I KNOW IT!

02:35.800 --> 02:40.033
BUT FOR NOW, WILL YOU PLEASE
JOIN ME IN FOOLING MYSELF?

02:40.033 --> 02:41.834
[ GIGGLING ]

02:44.900 --> 02:46.300
HA!
HA!

02:46.300 --> 02:48.000
♪ DO, DO, DO, DO, DO ♪
♪ DO, DO, DO, DO, DO ♪

02:48.000 --> 02:50.567
♪ DO, DO, DO, DO, DO ♪
♪ DO, DO, DO, DO, DO ♪

02:53.734 --> 02:54.967
FEE-NAY!

02:54.967 --> 02:57.600
FEE-EE-EE-NAY!

02:57.600 --> 02:59.500
[ High-pitched ]
FEENY!

02:59.500 --> 03:01.033
OOH, THAT WAS A NEW ONE!

03:03.867 --> 03:06.900
YOU ARE NOT CALLING A DUCK!

03:06.900 --> 03:08.800
ADMIT YOU LOVE
THE FEENY CALL.

03:08.800 --> 03:11.100
WE'RE NOT GONNA BE TOGETHER
MUCH LONGER,

03:11.100 --> 03:12.967
SO ADMIT IT
BEFORE IT'S TOO LATE.

03:12.967 --> 03:14.300
MR. FEENY.

03:14.300 --> 03:15.700
MR. FEENY!

03:15.700 --> 03:17.000
MR. FEENY!

03:17.000 --> 03:19.000
MR. FEENY!

03:19.000 --> 03:20.300
M--

03:20.300 --> 03:21.867
FEENY.

03:21.867 --> 03:24.400
F-F-F-F-EENY!

03:24.400 --> 03:25.867
FEE-NAY!

03:25.867 --> 03:28.700
FEE-EE-EE-EE-EE-NAY!

03:28.700 --> 03:31.400
WOW! HEY, HEY, HEY, WHAT?

03:31.400 --> 03:33.567
W-W-W-W-WHAT? WHAT?

03:33.567 --> 03:34.734
HEY! OW!

03:34.734 --> 03:37.900
[ HISSING ]

03:37.900 --> 03:39.200
OW!

03:39.200 --> 03:41.967
I LOVE THE FEENY CALL.

03:41.967 --> 03:45.233
I HAD A FEELING
YOU'D FEEL THAT WAY,

03:45.233 --> 03:47.600
SO I HAD THIS MADE FOR YOU.

03:47.600 --> 03:48.900
<i>FEE-NAY! </i>

03:48.900 --> 03:51.233
<i>FEE-HEE-HEE-HEE-NAY! </i>

03:51.233 --> 03:52.300
<i>FEENY! </i>

03:54.600 --> 03:57.200
BONE-CHILLING, MR. MATTHEWS.

03:57.200 --> 03:59.000
HEY, FEENY, LOOK.

03:59.000 --> 04:02.500
IT'S ERIC
DOING "MISSION: IMPOSSIBLE."

04:02.500 --> 04:04.233
OKAY, OKAY.

04:04.233 --> 04:06.734
ENOUGH OF THE LOVEFEST.
CAN YOU DO ME A FAVOR?

04:06.734 --> 04:09.033
CORY'S NOT DOING REAL WELL.
HE'S AFRAID OF CHANGE.

04:09.033 --> 04:10.834
JUST GIVE HIM THE USUAL.

04:19.600 --> 04:21.734
I'LL HAVE THE USUAL.

04:21.734 --> 04:23.567
HI, CORY.

04:23.567 --> 04:25.600
IT'S MR. MATTHEWS.
COME ON -- MR. MATTHEWS.

04:25.600 --> 04:27.867
I LIKE IT
WHEN YOU CALL ME MR. MATTHEWS.

04:27.867 --> 04:30.233
THAT'S WHAT YOU USED TO CALL ME.
THAT'S WHAT I WANT.

04:30.233 --> 04:32.600
FINE, MR. MATTHEWS.

04:32.600 --> 04:35.100
OKAY, WELL, COME ON.
STAND BY THE FENCE.

04:35.100 --> 04:38.500
YOUR BEST ADVICE ALWAYS CAME
RIGHT HERE FROM THE FENCE.

04:38.500 --> 04:40.500
HEY, MR. FEENY,
WHATCHA DOIN'?

04:40.500 --> 04:42.233
OKAY, WHAT CAN I DO FOR YOU?

04:42.233 --> 04:44.834
OKAY.

04:44.834 --> 04:47.900
TOPANGA'S GOT THIS JOB OFFER.

04:47.900 --> 04:50.400
SHE'S GOT AN INTERNSHIP
AT A LAW FIRM IN NEW YORK CITY.

04:50.400 --> 04:53.400
AND SHE TURNED IT DOWN.
AND SHE TURNED IT DOWN
BECAUSE OF ME.

04:53.400 --> 04:56.367
WAIT A MINUTE.
HOW -- HOW DID YOU KNOW THAT?

04:56.367 --> 05:00.133
WHAT IF SHE <i>DIDN'T </i>TURN IT
DOWN BECAUSE OF YOU?

05:00.133 --> 05:01.233
OF COURSE SHE DID.

05:01.233 --> 05:03.400
YOU'RE WRONG ABOUT THIS ONE,
MR. FEENY.

05:03.400 --> 05:04.734
YOU'RE REALLY SLIPPING.

05:04.734 --> 05:07.500
Okay, this is your moment.
Now, get me. Get me.

05:07.500 --> 05:10.567
[ SIGHS ]

05:10.567 --> 05:11.934
YOU SEE THAT FLOWER?

05:11.934 --> 05:15.667
YES! A GARDEN METAPHOR!
I <i>LOVE </i>THE GARDEN METAPHOR.

05:15.667 --> 05:17.100
I JUST LOVE THEM.

05:17.100 --> 05:20.000
THAT FLOWER WAS IN A SMALL POT
IN MY LIVING ROOM,

05:20.000 --> 05:22.100
BUT IT OUTGREW
ITS SURROUNDINGS,

05:22.100 --> 05:24.600
SO I TRANSPLANTED IT
HERE IN THE GARDEN.

05:24.600 --> 05:27.600
SEEMS LIKE IT'S DOING OKAY.

05:27.600 --> 05:29.834
OH, YES, IT'S FLOURISHING.

05:29.834 --> 05:32.934
NOW, TOPANGA
ALWAYS THRIVED HERE.

05:32.934 --> 05:36.467
SHE WAS SUCCESSFUL
IN WHATEVER SHE DID.

05:36.467 --> 05:37.834
HERE.

05:37.834 --> 05:43.000
WELL, I-I-I THINK
SHE'D BE SUCCESSFUL <i>ANYWHERE.  </i>

05:43.000 --> 05:44.567
DO YOU BELIEVE THAT?

05:44.567 --> 05:47.200
YEAH, OF COURSE I DO.

05:47.200 --> 05:48.600
DOES <i>SHE? </i>

05:48.600 --> 05:51.300
WHAT?

05:51.300 --> 05:52.667
DID YOU KNOW

05:52.667 --> 05:55.300
THAT, BEFORE SHE DECIDED
NOT TO GO TO YALE,

05:55.300 --> 05:57.600
SHE CAME TO MY OFFICE
TO TALK TO ME?

05:57.600 --> 05:59.200
ABOUT ME.

05:59.200 --> 06:01.600
SHE DIDN'T WANT TO GO TO YALE
BECAUSE OF ME.

06:01.600 --> 06:05.000
YES, THAT'S WHAT SHE <i>SAID.  </i>

06:05.000 --> 06:08.400
YOU MEAN, IT WASN'T ABOUT ME?

06:08.400 --> 06:10.000
NOW, WHEN I PULLED THE FLOWER

06:10.000 --> 06:12.200
OUT OF THE SMALL POT
IN MY LIVING ROOM,

06:12.200 --> 06:14.100
IT RESISTED A LITTLE,
YOU KNOW.

06:14.100 --> 06:16.200
IT TRIED TO HANG ON
BY ITS ROOTS.

06:16.200 --> 06:17.600
I HAD TO FORCE IT OUT.

06:17.600 --> 06:21.200
'CAUSE YOU THOUGHT
IT WOULD DO BETTER OUT HERE...

06:21.200 --> 06:22.767
IN THE WORLD, RIGHT?

06:22.767 --> 06:26.700
NO, BECAUSE I THOUGHT
IF I LEFT IT THERE,

06:26.700 --> 06:28.800
IT WOULD STOP GROWING.

06:31.934 --> 06:35.500
YOU'RE PUTTING MY PUNY PLANT
IN THE GROUND?

06:35.500 --> 06:39.200
YOUR PLANT, THOUGH IMMATURE
AND UNDEVELOPED,

06:39.200 --> 06:43.233
HAS WITHIN IT THE POTENTIAL
TO GROW AND FLOWER...

06:43.233 --> 06:46.300
WITH THE HELP
OF A PROPER GARDENER.

06:46.300 --> 06:49.033
YOU THINK SO?

06:49.033 --> 06:52.467
OH, YES. AS LONG AS NO ONE
WISHES IT ILL.

06:57.300 --> 07:00.300
HONEY, I HAVE NEVER FAILED
AT ANYTHING.

07:00.300 --> 07:02.233
NO. YOU'VE NEVER FAILED
AT ANYTHING,

07:02.233 --> 07:04.934
AND YOU NEVER WILL
AS LONG AS YOU STAY RIGHT HERE

07:04.934 --> 07:06.000
AND YOU PLAY IT SAFE.

07:09.734 --> 07:12.133
WELL, I WANT TO GO
TO NEW YORK.

07:12.133 --> 07:14.500
NO, YOU DON'T.

07:14.500 --> 07:16.033
I DO.

07:16.033 --> 07:19.300
I NEED ROOM TO GROW, TOPANGA,
AND I DON'T THINK IT'S FAIR

07:19.300 --> 07:21.500
THAT YOU'RE KEEPING ME
FROM GROWING.

07:21.500 --> 07:24.667
YOU WOULD DO THIS FOR ME?

07:24.667 --> 07:27.300
TOPANGA,
I'D DO ANYTHING FOR YOU.

07:27.300 --> 07:31.767
TOPANGA, IF I HAD TO DREAM UP
THE PERFECT WOMAN,

07:31.767 --> 07:35.500
SHE WOULDN'T EVEN
COME <i>CLOSE </i>TO YOU.

07:37.734 --> 07:40.567
WOULD YOU BE MY GIRLFRIEND?

07:48.767 --> 07:51.700
YES OR NO?

07:53.800 --> 07:55.200
CORY...

07:55.200 --> 07:57.500
MM-HMM.

07:57.500 --> 08:00.667
...I LOVE YOU, TOO.

08:00.667 --> 08:05.200
I WAS HOPING YOU DID.

08:14.200 --> 08:15.600
NO, Y-YOU'RE NOT MOVING,

08:15.600 --> 08:18.000
BECAUSE WE'RE SUPPOSED TO
BE TOGETHER,

08:18.000 --> 08:20.967
LIKE WE'VE ALWAYS TALKED ABOUT,
SO YOU <i>CAN'T </i>MOVE.

08:20.967 --> 08:23.467
BECAUSE WE DON'T DESERVE
THAT KIND OF PAIN.

08:23.467 --> 08:26.100
JUST GIVE ME A HUG AND A KISS
AND SAY GOODBYE TO ME.

08:26.100 --> 08:27.900
NO.

08:29.967 --> 08:31.800
CORY.

08:31.800 --> 08:33.800
TOPANGA.

08:36.667 --> 08:40.500
I MISSED YOU.
I MISSED YOU SO MUCH.

08:40.500 --> 08:42.233
I THINK IT'S A GOOD THING

08:42.233 --> 08:44.867
THAT CORY'S THE ONLY BOY
I'VE EVER LOVED.

08:44.867 --> 08:47.367
I WAS LOOKING FORWARD
TO DOING ALL OF THE THINGS

08:47.367 --> 08:49.200
THAT PEOPLE DO
WHO ARE IN LOVE...

08:49.200 --> 08:50.367
WITH CORY.

08:50.367 --> 08:52.967
YOU LIED TO TOPANGA!

08:52.967 --> 08:54.000
I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

08:54.000 --> 08:56.500
YOU LIED TO TOPANGA!

08:56.500 --> 08:58.700
SHAWN, ALL WE DID WAS TALK.

08:58.700 --> 08:59.967
ALL YOU DID WAS TALK?

08:59.967 --> 09:00.900
THAT'S IT.

09:00.900 --> 09:02.133
NO KISSY?
JUST TALKY.

09:02.133 --> 09:03.500
YOU <i>KISSED </i>HER?

09:03.500 --> 09:05.100
WHAT AM I GONNA DO?

09:05.100 --> 09:07.300
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT
YOU'RE <i>NOT </i>GONNA DO, CORY.

09:07.300 --> 09:09.000
YOU ARE NOT GONNA TELL
TOPANGA.

09:09.000 --> 09:10.600
I KNOW WOMEN, COR,

09:10.600 --> 09:13.200
AND I KNOW THAT SHE'LL FORGIVE
YOU FOR TALKING TO LAUREN.

09:13.200 --> 09:15.800
AND I KNOW THAT SHE'LL EVEN
FORGIVE YOU FOR LYING TO HER,

09:15.800 --> 09:17.300
BECAUSE
YOU NEVER HAVE BEFORE.

09:17.300 --> 09:19.100
BUT SHE WILL NEVER, EVER
FORGIVE YOU

09:19.100 --> 09:20.233
FOR KISSING ANOTHER GIRL.

09:20.233 --> 09:21.400
[ BANGS ]

09:21.400 --> 09:23.600
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU.

09:23.600 --> 09:24.834
ALL RIGHT.

09:24.834 --> 09:25.867
[ BANGS ]

09:25.867 --> 09:27.567
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU!

09:27.567 --> 09:29.900
WHEN WERE YOU
PLANNING ON TELLING ME

09:29.900 --> 09:31.767
ABOUT LAUREN'S LETTER?

09:31.767 --> 09:33.767
UH, UH, NOW.

09:33.767 --> 09:36.467
I-I WAS GONNA TELL YOU
ABOUT IT NOW.

09:36.467 --> 09:38.567
CORY, I HAVE NEVER ONCE
HAD TO WONDER

09:38.567 --> 09:40.467
IF YOU WERE TELLING ME
THE TRUTH.

09:40.467 --> 09:42.867
YOU KISSED HER
AND YOU LIED TO ME ABOUT IT.

09:42.867 --> 09:44.400
I DON'T KNOW
IF I TRUST YOU NOW.

09:44.400 --> 09:45.800
<i>SHE </i>KISSED <i>ME. </i>

09:45.800 --> 09:47.100
AND YOU MOVED AWAY?!

09:47.100 --> 09:49.000
WHAT DID YOU DO TO STOP HER?!

09:49.000 --> 09:50.934
NOTHING! NOTHING!

09:50.934 --> 09:52.834
I SAID,
"KISS ME, BABY, SWEETIE!

09:52.834 --> 09:54.233
"KILL THE RELATIONSHIP

09:54.233 --> 09:56.867
"WITH THE PERSON I CARE ABOUT
MORE THAN ANYTHING,

09:56.867 --> 09:59.400
AND MAKE ME MISERABLE
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE!"

09:59.400 --> 10:01.000
THAT'S WHAT I SAID!

10:01.000 --> 10:02.800
HER KISS MEANT <i>NOTHING </i>TO ME!

10:02.800 --> 10:04.567
COR, WHAT I'M
ABOUT TO TELL YOU

10:04.567 --> 10:06.600
IS GONNA MAKE YOU
WANT TO KILL ME.

10:06.600 --> 10:08.300
I'M NOT GONNA
KILL YOU, SHAWN.

10:08.300 --> 10:11.200
IT TAKES TOO MUCH TIME
TO BREAK IN A NEW BEST FRIEND.

10:11.200 --> 10:15.300
TOPANGA WENT OUT
WITH ANOTHER GUY LAST NIGHT.

10:15.300 --> 10:16.467
I'M SORRY.

10:16.467 --> 10:19.500
WE'RE THE ONLY TWO GUYS
IN THE WORLD

10:19.500 --> 10:21.767
WHO STILL THINK THERE'S HOPE
FOR ME AND TOPANGA.

10:21.767 --> 10:23.200
YOU'RE THROWING IN
THE TOWEL?

10:23.200 --> 10:26.233
YEAH, I AM.

10:26.233 --> 10:27.667
OKAY.

10:27.667 --> 10:29.767
THANK YOU.

10:29.767 --> 10:31.734
YOU OKAY?

10:31.734 --> 10:34.100
YEAH, SURE.

10:34.100 --> 10:36.467
IT'S AN INTERESTING FEELING,
THOUGH.

10:36.467 --> 10:38.200
WHAT, TO KNOW IT'S OVER?

10:38.200 --> 10:41.867
TO BE THE ONLY GUY IN THE WORLD
WHO KNOWS IT'S <i>NOT. </i>

10:41.867 --> 10:46.567
I LOVE YOU,
AND I WILL ALWAYS LOVE YOU.

10:46.567 --> 10:50.967
ANOTHER GUY KISSED YOU?

10:50.967 --> 10:52.200
YEAH.

10:52.200 --> 10:54.600
WANT TO DO SOMETHING
ABOUT IT?

11:03.700 --> 11:06.700
I FELT THAT, BOY.

11:06.700 --> 11:09.233
SO, ARE WE STARTING OVER?

11:09.233 --> 11:11.800
YEAH.

11:17.033 --> 11:18.500
MR. FEENY SAID
I SHOULD GO TO YALE

11:18.500 --> 11:20.300
UNLESS I HAVE
A REALLY GOOD REASON <i>NOT </i>TO.

11:20.300 --> 11:22.100
THERE ISN'T ANY GOOD REASON.

11:22.100 --> 11:23.133
ACTUALLY, THERE IS.

11:23.133 --> 11:24.667
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,

11:24.667 --> 11:29.033
THE JOHN ADAMS HIGH SCHOOL
CLASS OF 1998.

11:29.033 --> 11:32.133
WILL YOU MARRY ME?

11:32.133 --> 11:34.100
[ CHEERING ]

11:39.200 --> 11:42.767
WE WOULD LIKE YOUR BROTHER
TO BE YOUR BEST MAN.

11:42.767 --> 11:45.200
NO, ERIC! YOU'RE GONNA
KNOCK OVER THE CANDLE!

11:45.200 --> 11:46.767
OHH!

11:46.767 --> 11:49.100
♪ FOR HE'S
A JOLLY GOOD FELLOW ♪

11:49.100 --> 11:50.900
♪ FOR HE'S
A JOLLY GOOD FELLOW ♪

11:50.900 --> 11:53.400
OH, MY GOD.
LOOK, IT'S HAPPENING.

11:53.400 --> 11:56.667
ERIC, LOOK WHAT YOU DID!
ERIC!

11:56.667 --> 11:58.133
♪ THE CURTAINS ARE ON FIRE ♪

11:58.133 --> 12:00.400
♪ THE CURTAINS ARE ON FIRE ♪

12:00.400 --> 12:01.967
AAH! AAH!

12:01.967 --> 12:04.200
♪ THEY'RE CHOPPIN' UP
THE DORM ROOM ♪

12:04.200 --> 12:05.800
♪ THEY'RE CHOPPIN' UP
THE DORM ROOM ♪

12:05.800 --> 12:08.500
♪ MY BROTHER IS A MORON! ♪

12:08.500 --> 12:10.400
♪ WHICH NOBODY CAN DENY ♪

12:10.400 --> 12:12.100
[ LAUGHS ]

12:12.100 --> 12:13.567
AAH!

12:15.400 --> 12:16.900
HE'S OUT, SHAWN'S IN!

12:16.900 --> 12:19.467
SOMEBODY SAVE THE BABY!
SOMEBODY SAVE THE BABY!

12:19.467 --> 12:24.400
THAT IS THE MOST BEAUTIFUL DRESS
I'VE EVER SEEN.

12:25.500 --> 12:27.200
BITE ME.

12:29.700 --> 12:32.700
I WASN'T SURE THIS DAY
WOULD EVER COME...

12:32.700 --> 12:34.900
BUT YOU WERE.

12:34.900 --> 12:37.200
I WASN'T SURE
THAT LOVE COULD SURVIVE

12:37.200 --> 12:39.500
EVERYTHING
THAT WE PUT IT THROUGH...

12:39.500 --> 12:41.033
BUT YOU WERE.

12:41.033 --> 12:44.500
YOU WERE ALWAYS STRONG
AND ALWAYS SURE.

12:44.500 --> 12:47.200
AND NOW I KNOW THAT I WANT YOU
TO STAND BESIDE ME

12:47.200 --> 12:49.767
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE.

12:49.767 --> 12:51.600
THAT'S WHAT I'M SURE OF.

12:56.600 --> 13:00.700
I HAVE TO TALK TO <i>HER </i>NOW,
OKAY?

13:00.700 --> 13:01.934
GO AHEAD.

13:01.934 --> 13:04.100
EVER SINCE I WAS YOUNG,

13:04.100 --> 13:08.767
I NEVER REALLY UNDERSTOOD
ANYTHING ABOUT THE WORLD.

13:08.767 --> 13:13.800
AND I NEVER UNDERSTOOD ANYTHING
THAT HAPPENED IN MY LIFE.

13:13.800 --> 13:19.300
THE <i>ONLY </i>THING THAT EVER MADE
SENSE TO ME WAS YOU

13:19.300 --> 13:23.033
AND HOW I FELT ABOUT YOU.

13:23.033 --> 13:24.934
[ SNIFFLES ]

13:24.934 --> 13:29.600
THAT'S...ALL I'VE EVER KNOWN.

13:29.600 --> 13:32.767
AND THAT'S ENOUGH.

13:32.767 --> 13:34.133
THAT'S ENOUGH FOR ME

13:34.133 --> 13:36.600
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE,
TOPANGA.

13:38.867 --> 13:40.967
CORY, I'M SCARED.

13:40.967 --> 13:42.967
I KNOW YOU ARE.

13:42.967 --> 13:44.700
WHAT IF I FAIL?

13:44.700 --> 13:48.834
WELL, IF YOU FAIL,
THEN I'LL SEE THIS GIRL

13:48.834 --> 13:52.100
WHO TOOK A REAL RISK,
YOU KNOW,

13:52.100 --> 13:55.000
WHO LEFT THE WORLD
SHE WAS USED TO

13:55.000 --> 13:56.700
WITH GREAT COURAGE,

13:56.700 --> 13:59.767
AND SHE DANCED THE DANCE,
YOU KNOW?

13:59.767 --> 14:01.233
AND IF YOU FAIL,

14:01.233 --> 14:04.300
I THINK THERE'S A REAL CHANCE
I'LL LOVE YOU EVEN MORE.

14:07.500 --> 14:09.000
WE'RE GOING TO NEW YORK.

14:09.000 --> 14:13.100
WE ARE GOING TO START
THE NEXT CHAPTER OF OUR LIVES.

14:13.100 --> 14:14.700
HOW AM I TAKING IT?

14:14.700 --> 14:16.500
BETTER THAN ME.

14:16.500 --> 14:17.967
LET'S HUG.

14:17.967 --> 14:19.300
[ SQUEALING ]

14:19.300 --> 14:20.934
MAY I HAVE THIS DANCE?

14:20.934 --> 14:23.233
I THOUGHT YOU'D NEVER ASK.

14:33.400 --> 14:36.400
NEW YORK IS CRAZY!
THEY'RE JUST BABIES!

14:36.400 --> 14:38.000
THERE'S NO BABIES
IN NEW YORK!

14:38.000 --> 14:39.767
THE RATS EAT THEM!

14:39.767 --> 14:42.500
MOM, GET AHOLD OF YOURSELF.
YOU'RE PSYCHO.

14:42.500 --> 14:45.500
OH, THAT'S VERY NICE.
YOUR MOTHER IS PSYCHO.

14:45.500 --> 14:47.300
OH, NOW I'M PSYCHO, ALAN.

14:47.300 --> 14:50.200
DON'T CALL YOUR MOTHER PSYCHO.
IT'S NOT NICE.

14:50.200 --> 14:54.033
CORY AND TOPANGA
ARE GOING TO THE BIG CITY,

14:54.033 --> 14:56.767
AND [SOBBING]
I'M INCONSOLABLE!

14:58.200 --> 15:00.367
ERIC'S DECIDED
TO GO WITH THEM.

15:00.367 --> 15:03.600
OH.

15:03.600 --> 15:07.867
SO, WHAT'S FOR LUNCH?

15:07.867 --> 15:09.734
YOU'RE GOING
INTO THE PEACE CORPS?

15:09.734 --> 15:12.000
I THOUGHT YOU WERE GONNA
TRAVEL THE WORLD.

15:12.000 --> 15:13.567
WELL, I WILL, I WILL.

15:13.567 --> 15:16.033
RIGHT AFTER
I DO SOME GOOD IN IT.

15:17.700 --> 15:21.667
"I'M...CHUCKING...
TO DEATH."

15:21.667 --> 15:22.800
HMM.

15:22.800 --> 15:25.834
OH, GOD!
OH, GOD. OKAY!

15:25.834 --> 15:29.700
WHOO! IT'S OFFICIALLY OVER.

15:29.700 --> 15:30.600
AAH!!

15:33.200 --> 15:34.967
NEW PLAN!

15:34.967 --> 15:37.700
AAH! AAH!

15:37.700 --> 15:39.667
AAH!!

15:39.667 --> 15:41.200
PIE HER!

15:41.200 --> 15:43.867
PIE HER! PIE HER!

15:43.867 --> 15:44.867
PIE!

15:44.867 --> 15:46.133
PIE!

15:46.133 --> 15:47.934
DON'T TREAT ME SPECIAL
'CAUSE I'M A WOMAN!

15:47.934 --> 15:49.900
SHE'S RIGHT!

15:49.900 --> 15:51.734
I'M NOT YOUR MOTHER,
I'M YOUR ROOMMATE!

15:51.734 --> 15:52.867
YEAH!

15:52.867 --> 15:55.400
NOW HIT JACK WITH THE PIE.

16:00.066 --> 16:02.233
OKAY.
THAT'S ABOUT EVERYTHING.

16:02.233 --> 16:05.000
I CAN'T BELIEVE
WE'RE ACTUALLY DOING THIS.

16:05.000 --> 16:07.467
THIS IS THE RIGHT MOVE FOR ME.
NEW YORK CITY.

16:07.467 --> 16:10.300
NOBODY KNOWS ME THERE.
I CAN BE ANYBODY I WANT TO BE.

16:10.300 --> 16:12.600
I WANT YOU TO BE ERIC.

16:12.600 --> 16:16.000
♪ BLEH, BLEH, BLEH,
MEH, MEH, MEH ♪

16:16.000 --> 16:18.600
♪ BLEH, BLEH, BZZ-BZZ-BZZ ♪

16:23.600 --> 16:25.300
HELLO, ROOMIE!
AAH!

16:25.300 --> 16:26.400
ROOMIE?

16:26.400 --> 16:27.867
AY-Y-Y-E!

16:27.867 --> 16:30.567
RACHEL, WHAT IS
ERIC'S FAVORITE FISH?

16:30.567 --> 16:34.867
PENGUIN.

16:34.867 --> 16:38.000
NO, I DON'T THINK
YOU UNDERSTOOD.

16:38.000 --> 16:39.500
BAM! HA HA HA!

16:39.500 --> 16:40.934
[ Laughing ] PENGUIN!

16:40.934 --> 16:42.300
I KNOW MY MAN!

16:42.300 --> 16:43.300
IT'S LIKE WE HAVE
ONE BRAIN.

16:43.300 --> 16:46.100
YES, BUT, SEE, YOU'RE ALREADY
IN A NEW RELATIONSHIP.

16:46.100 --> 16:47.667
YOU'RE IN A TRIANGLE, FEENY.

16:47.667 --> 16:50.700
AND TAKE IT FROM SOMEBODY
WHO'S BEEN IN A TRIANGLE BEFORE,

16:50.700 --> 16:52.033
HE WHO HESITATES IS LOST.

16:52.033 --> 16:53.367
RACHEL!

16:53.367 --> 16:55.800
[ SOBBING ]

16:55.800 --> 16:56.967
I'M OKAY, I'M OKAY.

16:56.967 --> 17:00.400
CHECK! WILL SOMEONE
PLEASE BRING ME A CHECK?!

17:00.400 --> 17:02.867
PTT-A-Y-Y-E!

17:02.867 --> 17:03.867
MATTHEWS!

17:03.867 --> 17:04.934
SIR, YES, SIR!

17:04.934 --> 17:07.200
YOU ARE A DISGRACE
TO THIS UNIVERSITY,

17:07.200 --> 17:09.600
TO THIS COUNTRY,
AND HUMANITY IN GENERAL!

17:09.600 --> 17:12.500
[ Laughing ] WOW.

17:12.500 --> 17:14.000
HAH-SIKE!

17:15.400 --> 17:17.734
TALKITY-TALK!
TALKITY-TALK-TALK-TALK!

17:17.734 --> 17:20.233
OH, LOOK! TRAILER BOY'S GOT
ALL THE ANSWERS!

17:20.233 --> 17:22.400
YOU KNOW SOMETHING,
TRAILER BOY?

17:22.400 --> 17:24.367
THERE'S ONE THING
YOU DON'T HAVE.

17:24.367 --> 17:25.500
BAM! PENNY!

17:41.300 --> 17:43.000
YOU NEVER BREASTFED ME!

17:43.000 --> 17:45.867
WE'RE IN THE MIDDLE OF A SERIOUS
FAMILY DISCUSSION HERE.

17:47.467 --> 17:50.133
WELL...

17:50.133 --> 17:52.100
I'M GOING TO NEW YORK.

17:52.100 --> 17:55.133
GOOD.

17:55.133 --> 17:57.400
SEE YA, PAL.

17:58.567 --> 18:00.200
HEY, ERIC,
NICE TO MEET YOU.

18:00.200 --> 18:02.100
NICE TO MEET YOU, TOO,
JACK.

18:02.100 --> 18:03.367
YOU SMOKE?

18:03.367 --> 18:04.800
NO. YOU SMOKE?

18:04.800 --> 18:05.900
NO.

18:05.900 --> 18:07.500
DO YOU LIKE PETS?

18:07.500 --> 18:10.400
NAH. I HAVE A HARD ENOUGH TIME
KEEPING TRACK OF MYSELF.

18:10.400 --> 18:11.800
YOU?

18:11.800 --> 18:14.300
I'M NOT A PET GUY.
I GOT FOUR KIDS, THOUGH.

18:14.300 --> 18:16.800
[ LAUGHS ]

18:16.800 --> 18:19.500
I THOUGHT IT WAS FUNNY.

18:19.500 --> 18:22.700
FAVORITE COLOR ON THREE.
GO.

18:22.700 --> 18:24.000
1, 2, 3
--1, 2, 3 --

18:24.000 --> 18:25.233
BLUE!
BLUE!

18:25.233 --> 18:26.600
SEE YOU LATER, MAN.

18:26.600 --> 18:28.233
YEAH, NICE TO MEET YOU.

18:28.233 --> 18:29.367
I DON'T LIKE HIM.

18:29.367 --> 18:31.834
GIVE ME MY NUMBERS!

18:31.834 --> 18:34.400
OW! OW! OW! OW! OW!

18:34.400 --> 18:36.767
YOU DON'T GET IT.
WE'RE IN COLLEGE NOW.

18:36.767 --> 18:39.100
WE'RE BEING JUDGED
ON A WHOLE NEW LEVEL.

18:39.100 --> 18:41.600
THEORIES AND FOOTNOTES,
SHADES OF MEANING,

18:41.600 --> 18:42.867
NUANCE, SPELLING!

18:42.867 --> 18:44.967
WHERE DOES IT END?!
WHERE DOES IT END?!

18:44.967 --> 18:46.934
OW! OW! OW! OW!

18:46.934 --> 18:49.400
I LOVE YOU, MAN.

18:49.400 --> 18:53.100
DUDE, DON'T EVEN, MAN.
I'M THE ONE <i>THAT LOVES YOU.  </i>

18:53.100 --> 18:54.300
DUDE!

18:54.300 --> 18:56.934
DUDE!
DUDE!

18:56.934 --> 18:58.967
Rachel: I CAN'T FIGURE OUT
HOW TO WORK

18:58.967 --> 19:00.367
THE STOPPER IN THE BATHTUB.

19:00.367 --> 19:01.467
CAN ONE OF YOU SHOW ME?

19:11.500 --> 19:14.100
OKAY, WELL,
THE BEST GOODBYES

19:14.100 --> 19:15.300
ARE FAST GOODBYES.

19:15.300 --> 19:18.000
ARE YOU FREAKING NUTS?

19:19.667 --> 19:21.734
WHERE IS YOUR SOUL?!

19:21.734 --> 19:26.967
YOU'RE JUST GONNA CAST ME ASIDE
LIKE AN OLD PAIR OF SHOES?!

19:26.967 --> 19:30.500
WE HAVE TO SAY GOODBYE
FOR AN HOUR!

19:30.500 --> 19:33.467
GUYS,
IT'S ONLY 70 MILES AWAY.

19:33.467 --> 19:35.367
[ Voice breaking ]
NO, NO, NO!

19:35.367 --> 19:36.500
I WAS DOING IT QUICK

19:36.500 --> 19:39.467
BECAUSE I THOUGHT
YOU WANTED TO DO IT QUICK!

19:39.467 --> 19:42.667
I WANT A DIVORCE.

19:42.667 --> 19:47.700
OKAY, I'M HERE.
WHAT'S THE BIG EMERGENCY?

19:47.700 --> 19:50.200
COME ON.
YOU'RE MY BEST FRIEND, MAN.

19:50.200 --> 19:52.100
YOU JUST GOT TO LOOSEN UP.

19:52.100 --> 19:54.300
YOU DON'T THINK I'M A GEEK?

19:54.300 --> 19:55.400
OF COURSE NOT.

19:55.400 --> 19:57.133
YOU THINK I'M COOL?

19:57.133 --> 19:58.400
OF COURSE NOT.

19:58.400 --> 20:00.300
THEN WHAT AM I?

20:00.300 --> 20:02.967
YOU'RE CORY. I'M SHAWN.
JUST LIKE IT'S ALWAYS BEEN.

20:02.967 --> 20:04.767
WHAT ELSE
DO YOU NEED TO KNOW?

20:05.467 --> 20:07.600
Girl: FIGHT! FIGHT!

20:07.600 --> 20:11.000
[ SHOUTING ]

20:11.000 --> 20:12.500
BREAK IT UP! BREAK IT UP!

20:12.500 --> 20:16.233
GET BACK TO CLASS NOW.

20:16.233 --> 20:18.734
HUNTER? MATTHEWS?

20:18.734 --> 20:21.033
DID YOU GUYS KNOW
YOU WERE FIGHTING EACH OTHER?

20:21.033 --> 20:23.567
I was hoping
you'd come alone.

20:23.567 --> 20:25.100
You-know-who
wouldn't hear of it.

20:25.100 --> 20:26.500
I think she suspects.

20:26.500 --> 20:28.600
Hey, I understand
that she's important to you.

20:28.600 --> 20:30.467
We both knew
this would happen eventually.

20:30.467 --> 20:31.500
Getting older.

20:31.500 --> 20:32.700
Meeting girls.

20:32.700 --> 20:34.567
Having relationships
with those girls.

20:34.567 --> 20:38.400
Which means there's less time
for best friends...

20:38.400 --> 20:39.800
to spend time together.

20:39.800 --> 20:40.934
It's only natural.

20:40.934 --> 20:42.400
Sure, natural.

20:42.400 --> 20:45.900
Hey, that cinnabun was for me,
wasn't it?

20:45.900 --> 20:49.400
Cory...

20:49.400 --> 20:51.400
ZZBBBBZZZ!

20:51.400 --> 20:53.000
YIP YIP-YIP-YIP-YIP!
ZZBBBBZZZ!

20:53.000 --> 20:55.233
ZZBBBBZZZ!

20:55.233 --> 20:57.400
YIP YIP-YIP-YIP-YIP!
ZZBBBBZZZ!

20:57.400 --> 20:58.734
INTERESTING.

20:58.734 --> 21:01.233
IN <i>MY </i>CLASS, MR. HUNTER
HANDLES THE YIPPING.

21:05.934 --> 21:10.867
SHAWN! SHAWN,
IT'S BOTH OF THEM!

21:10.867 --> 21:14.600
OH, NO. NOW I DON'T KNOW
WHICH CLASS I SLEPT THROUGH.

21:29.600 --> 21:31.100
AAH!
FEENY LEFT US
THE KEYS TO HIS HOUSE.

21:31.100 --> 21:34.100
HE <i>KNOWS </i>THIS IS GONNA HAPPEN.
HE <i>WANTS </i>THIS TO HAPPEN.

21:34.100 --> 21:36.400
AAH!

21:36.400 --> 21:38.900
CORY, IF YOU'RE GONNA STAY
AT MY BED AND BREAKFAST,

21:38.900 --> 21:40.000
KEEP YOUR VOICE DOWN.

21:40.000 --> 21:41.900
THE MOREPARKS
ARE UPSTAIRS NAPPING.

21:41.900 --> 21:44.100
Aah!

21:44.934 --> 21:46.900
AAH!

21:46.900 --> 21:47.800
OHH!

21:47.800 --> 21:50.033
MY ROOM HERE IS A --
A <i>SHRINE </i>

21:50.033 --> 21:51.934
TO MY MEDIOCRE LIFE.

21:51.934 --> 21:53.834
LET'S STOP RIGHT THERE,
OKAY?

21:53.834 --> 21:55.867
YOU DON'T HAVE
A MEDIOCRE LIFE.

21:55.867 --> 21:57.500
THERE'S NOTHING ABOUT ME

21:57.500 --> 22:00.200
THAT SEPARATES ME
FROM ANYBODY ELSE.

22:03.300 --> 22:05.233
UNDERPANTS!

22:05.233 --> 22:07.834
YOU SHOWED HIM THAT?!

22:07.834 --> 22:11.734
HEY! HOW COME
I NEVER GET TO SEE NOTHIN'?!

22:11.734 --> 22:13.600
[ Shouting ]
HOW LONG YOU BEEN MARRIED?!

22:13.600 --> 22:15.667
WHO?!

22:15.667 --> 22:17.600
WHAT?!

22:17.600 --> 22:21.233
THEY <i>WANT </i>YOU
TO TAKE THE ROLLS!

22:21.233 --> 22:23.300
SO, THIS IS IT?

22:23.300 --> 22:25.033
YES, THIS IS...

22:25.033 --> 22:27.000
GOODBYE.

22:27.000 --> 22:29.967
OH, THAT'S IT.
I CAN'T TAKE THIS ANYMORE.

22:29.967 --> 22:31.767
HERE, THIS IS FOR YOU.

22:31.767 --> 22:32.734
WHAT'S THAT?

22:32.734 --> 22:33.967
HIS STUFF.

22:33.967 --> 22:36.100
YOU'RE COMING WITH US?

22:36.100 --> 22:37.767
I'M GOING WITH YOU?

22:37.767 --> 22:38.600
REALLY?

22:38.600 --> 22:40.967
YAY!
YAY!

22:40.967 --> 22:44.500
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

22:44.500 --> 22:47.100
I CAN'T DO THIS.
I'VE GOT A LIFE HERE, CORY.

22:47.100 --> 22:49.100
I CAN'T JUST PACK UP
AND LEAVE.

22:49.100 --> 22:51.400
I MEAN, I'VE GOT
A MOTHER AND A FATHER

22:51.400 --> 22:53.200
AND A GIRLFRIEND
AND A GOOD JOB.

22:53.200 --> 22:55.100
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

22:55.100 --> 22:58.100
DO YOU REALLY LIKE HER?

22:58.100 --> 23:01.800
YEAH, I REALLY DO.
